quizzes.question:
Fill in the blank to print ''World'' to the screen.
[!raw!]
<?php 
  $Hello = "World";
  $a = "Hello";
  echo {0}a; 
?>

quizzes.textContent:
[h1]Variable Variables[/h1]

With PHP, you can use one variable to specify another variable's name. 
So, a [b]variable variable [/b]treats the value of another variable as its name.

[b]For example:[/b] [code format="php" codeId="468"]<?php
  $a = 'hello';
  $hello = "Hi!";
  echo [b]$$a[/b];

  // Outputs '[b]Hi!'[/b]
?>[/code]
[note][b]$$a [/b]is a variable that is using the value of another variable, [b]$a[/b], as its name. The value of [b]$a[/b] is equal to "hello". The resulting variable is [b]$hello[/b], which holds the value "Hi!".[/note]
